OL,6,F"The stand-out feature of the
OL,7,Foffending was the enormous indirect
OL,8,F'societal' harm caused by the loss to
OL,9,Fpublic confidence in the police," she
OL,10,Fadded.
OL,12,FBaroness Carr continued: "In
OL,13,Fdetermining whether a message is
OL,14,F'grossly offensive' the tribunal of
OL,15,Ffact must ask whether its contents are
OL,16,Fliable to cause gross offence to those
OL,17,Fto whom it relates, or whether
OL,18,Freasonable persons in our society
OL,19,Fwould find it grossly offensive."
