OL,6,FIn their written judgment, Baroness
OL,7,FCarr and Mr Justice Saini also said:
OL,8,F"On the facts of this case, given that
OL,9,Fthe messages were intended to be
OL,10,F'darkly humorous' jokes and the
OL,11,Frecipients of the messages were found
OL,12,Fby the judge to have shared the
OL,13,Fappellants' sense of humour, no
OL,14,Fassistance could be gained from their
OL,15,Freaction to determine whether the
OL,16,Fmessages were 'grossly offensive' in
OL,17,Fthe eyes of a reasonable member of the
OL,18,Fpublic, judged by the standards of
OL,19,Ftoday's society."
OL,26,@pD@AOU{D@QO]
