OL,6,FShe said in written submissions: "The
OL,7,Fprovision is not exclusively concerned
OL,8,Fwith protecting people from receipt of
OL,9,Funsolicited messages of the proscribed
OL,10,Fcharacter, but is rather aimed at
OL,11,Fensuring propriety in communications
OL,12,Fover electronic public networks."
OL,14,FThe court was told that in one
OL,15,Fexchange, Borders wrote: "I can't wait
OL,16,Fto get on guns so I can shoot some
OL,17,Fc*** in the face!"
